line_1: With her Soul charming naked Limbs:
There let me bathe my yet unhallow'd limbs,
line_2: Where on the surface Lead, like feathers, swims;

line_1: Pain with strong grasp distorts his writhing limbs,
line_2: And instant, lo, his dizzy eye-ball swims

line_1: Slackens their sinews, and benumbs their limbs;
line_2: To the high throne of sense soft slumber climbs,

line_1: And gaze enamour'd on her silver limbs.
line_2: Surround the timorous Beauty, as she swims,

line_1: Bursts o'er their heads, inhumes their struggling limbs;
line_2: Wave over wave the driving desert swims,

line_1: Chills their pale bosoms, bathes their shuddering limbs,
line_2: Through gaping seams the rushing deluge swims,

line_1: Spreads o'er the shuddering Line his shadowy limbs,
line_2: And Frost and Famine follow as he swims. —

line_1: Helm'd with broad tail, and oar'd with giant limbs;
line_2: High on the flood with speckled bosom swims,
The warrior's scar not half so graceful seems,

line_1: And nerves Herculean bend her sinewy limbs;
line_2: O'er her warm cheek the blush of beauty swims,

line_1: And feels new vigour stretch his swelling limbs;
line_2: Pleased on the boiling wave old AESON swims,

line_1: And the clear stream betrays her snowy limbs.
line_2: Loose o'er the flood her azure mantle swims,

line_1: Cold sweats bedew the trembling limbs;
line_2: The head in wild distraction swims;

line_1: While he scarce trails along his tortur'd Limbs;
line_2: Swift up her pendant Web Arachne climbs,

line_1: Her dancing taper over outstretch'd limbs,
line_2: No idling hours are here, when Fancy trims
